#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.24:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Uruvelavagga"
msgstr "3. At Uruvelā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Kāḷakārāmasutta"
msgstr "24. At Kāḷaka’s Monastery"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: kāḷakārāme → koḷikārāme (mr)
msgctxt "an4.24:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sākete viharati kāḷakārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāketa, in Kāḷaka’s monastery."

msgctxt "an4.24:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an4.24:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an4.24:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an4.24:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca—"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.24:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevakassa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tamahaṃ jānāmi."
msgstr ""
"“In this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its "
"ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—whatever is seen, heard, thought, "
"cognized, searched, and explored by the mind: that I know."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.24:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevakassa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tamahaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"In this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its "
"ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—whatever is seen, heard, thought, "
"cognized, searched, and explored by the mind: that I have insight into."

msgctxt "an4.24:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ tathāgatassa viditaṃ, taṃ tathāgato na upaṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"That has been known by a Realized One, but a Realized One is not subject to "
"it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.24:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevakassa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tamahaṃ na jānāmīti vadeyyaṃ, taṃ "
"mamassa musā."
msgstr ""
"If I were to say that ‘I do not know … the world with its gods’, I would be "
"lying."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: tampassa → taṃ pissa (s1-3, km) | taṃ mamassa (mr)
msgctxt "an4.24:5.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave … pe … tamahaṃ jānāmi ca na ca jānāmīti vadeyyaṃ, tampassa "
"tādisameva."
msgstr ""
"If I were to say that ‘I both know and do not know … the world with its gods’"
", that would be just the same."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.24:6.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave … pe … tamahaṃ neva jānāmi na na jānāmīti vadeyyaṃ, taṃ "
"mamassa kali."
msgstr ""
"If I were to say that ‘I neither know nor do not know … the world with its "
"gods’, that would be my fault."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.24:7.1"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato daṭṭhā daṭṭhabbaṃ, diṭṭhaṃ na maññati, "
"adiṭṭhaṃ na maññati, daṭṭhabbaṃ na maññati, daṭṭhāraṃ na maññati;"
msgstr ""
"So a Realized One sees what’s to be seen, but does not conceive what’s seen, "
"does not conceive what’s unseen, does not conceive what’s to be seen, and "
"does not conceive a seer."

msgctxt "an4.24:7.2"
msgid ""
"sutvā sotabbaṃ, sutaṃ na maññati, asutaṃ na maññati, sotabbaṃ na maññati, "
"sotāraṃ na maññati;"
msgstr ""
"He hears what’s to be heard, but does not conceive what’s heard, does not "
"conceive what’s unheard, does not conceive what’s to be heard, and does not "
"conceive a hearer."

msgctxt "an4.24:7.3"
msgid ""
"mutvā motabbaṃ, mutaṃ na maññati, amutaṃ na maññati, motabbaṃ na maññati, "
"motāraṃ na maññati;"
msgstr ""
"He thinks what’s to be thought, but does not conceive what’s thought, does "
"not conceive what’s not thought, does not conceive what’s to be thought, and "
"does not conceive a thinker."

msgctxt "an4.24:7.4"
msgid ""
"viññatvā viññātabbaṃ, viññātaṃ na maññati, aviññātaṃ na maññati, viññātabbaṃ "
"na maññati, viññātāraṃ na maññati."
msgstr ""
"He knows what’s to be known, but does not conceive what’s known, does not "
"conceive what’s unknown, does not conceive what’s to be known, and does not "
"conceive a knower."

#. VAR: tādīyeva tādī → tādisova tādī (s1-3, km) | tādise yeva tādi (pts1) | tādīyeva tādīyevekā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.24:7.5"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato diṭṭhasutamutaviññātabbesu dhammesu tādīyeva "
"tādī."
msgstr ""
"Since a Realized One is poised in the midst of things seen, heard, thought, "
"and known, he is the poised one."

#. VAR: tādimhā → tāditamhā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.24:7.6"
msgid ""
"‘Tamhā ca pana tādimhā añño tādī uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthī’ti "
"vadāmīti."
msgstr "And I say that there is no-one who has better or finer poise than this."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.24:8.1"
msgid "Yaṃ kiñci diṭṭhaṃva sutaṃ mutaṃ vā,"
msgstr "The poised one does not take anything"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.24:8.2"
msgid "Ajjhositaṃ saccamutaṃ paresaṃ;"
msgstr "seen, heard, or thought to be ultimately true or false."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.24:8.3"
msgid "Na tesu tādī sayasaṃvutesu,"
msgstr "But others get attached, thinking it’s the truth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.24:8.4"
msgid "Saccaṃ musā vāpi paraṃ daheyya."
msgstr "limited by their preconceptions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: paṭikacca → paṭigacca (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.24:9.1"
msgid "Etañca sallaṃ paṭikacca disvā,"
msgstr "Since they’ve already seen this dart,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.24:9.2"
msgid "Ajjhositā yattha pajā visattā;"
msgstr "to which people are attached and cling,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.24:9.3"
msgid "Jānāmi passāmi tatheva etaṃ,"
msgstr "they say, ‘I know, I see, that’s how it is’;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.24:9.4"
msgid "Ajjhositaṃ natthi tathāgatānan”ti."
msgstr "the Realized Ones have no attachments.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.24:9.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
